<h1>SDKs & Libraries</h1>
<p class="lead">
    Use standard OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect libraries to integrate with Harker Identity.
</p>

<div class="docs-callout docs-callout-info">
    <p>Harker Identity is fully compatible with any OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect compliant library. Use your preferred library for your platform.</p>
</div>

<h2>JavaScript / TypeScript</h2>

<div class="row g-3">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="docs-card">
            <h4><i class="bi bi-box me-2"></i>oidc-client-ts</h4>
            <p>Full-featured OpenID Connect client for browser-based applications.</p>
            <pre><code>npm install oidc-client-ts</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="docs-card">
            <h4><i class="bi bi-box me-2"></i>@@auth0/auth0-spa-js</h4>
            <p>Lightweight SDK that works with any OIDC provider.</p>
            <pre><code>npm install @@auth0/auth0-spa-js</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Example: React with oidc-client-ts</h3>
<pre><code>import { UserManager, WebStorageStateStore } from 'oidc-client-ts';

const userManager = new UserManager({
  authority: 'https://your-identity-server.com',
  client_id: 'your-client-id',
  redirect_uri: 'https://yourapp.com/callback',
  scope: 'openid profile email',
  userStore: new WebStorageStateStore({ store: window.localStorage })
});

// Login
await userManager.signinRedirect();

// Handle callback
const user = await userManager.signinRedirectCallback();
console.log('Logged in as:', user.profile.name);</code></pre>

<h2>.NET</h2>

<div class="docs-card">
    <h4><i class="bi bi-microsoft me-2"></i>Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.OpenIdConnect</h4>
    <p>Built-in ASP.NET Core middleware for OpenID Connect authentication.</p>
    <pre><code>dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.OpenIdConnect</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Example: ASP.NET Core</h3>
<pre><code>builder.Services.AddAuthentication(options =>
{
    options.DefaultScheme = CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme;
    options.DefaultChallengeScheme = OpenIdConnectDefaults.AuthenticationScheme;
})
.AddCookie()
.AddOpenIdConnect(options =>
{
    options.Authority = "https://your-identity-server.com";
    options.ClientId = "your-client-id";
    options.ClientSecret = "your-client-secret";
    options.ResponseType = "code";
    options.Scope.Add("profile");
    options.Scope.Add("email");
    options.SaveTokens = true;
});</code></pre>

<h2>Python</h2>

<div class="docs-card">
    <h4><i class="bi bi-filetype-py me-2"></i>Authlib</h4>
    <p>Comprehensive OAuth/OIDC library for Python applications.</p>
    <pre><code>pip install authlib</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Example: Flask</h3>
<pre><code>from authlib.integrations.flask_client import OAuth

oauth = OAuth(app)
oauth.register(
    name='tgharker',
    client_id='your-client-id',
    client_secret='your-client-secret',
    server_metadata_url='https://your-identity-server.com/.well-known/openid-configuration',
    client_kwargs={'scope': 'openid profile email'}
)

@@app.route('/login')
def login():
    redirect_uri = url_for('callback', _external=True)
    return oauth.tgharker.authorize_redirect(redirect_uri)</code></pre>

<h2>Java / Kotlin</h2>

<div class="docs-card">
    <h4><i class="bi bi-cup-hot me-2"></i>Spring Security OAuth2</h4>
    <p>Spring Security's built-in OAuth2/OIDC support.</p>
    <pre><code>implementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-oauth2-client'</code></pre>
</div>

<h3>Example: Spring Boot</h3>
<pre><code>spring:
  security:
    oauth2:
      client:
        registration:
          tgharker:
            client-id: your-client-id
            client-secret: your-client-secret
            scope: openid,profile,email
        provider:
          tgharker:
            issuer-uri: https://your-identity-server.com</code></pre>

